$interpreted: Ralph: Have you heard about the rumor that a member of the Feather Clan ahs appeared in the Slums?
Aosta: We'll talk about it later. Business first.
Aosta: Found it.
Aosta: Tie it up.
Ralph: You want me to do it!? For what?
Aosta: To use as catalyst. After you're done with it, follow me.
Ralph: So, what is this now?
Aosta: Preparation for the Feather Clan  rumor you just mentioned. This is a piece of stone retrieved from door of an Atlas relic site.
Aosta: When it comes near the blood of Feather Clan member, it will trigger a reaction. Then we use the monster as a catalyst to enhance the reaction...
Ralph: Amazing! This way we can detect their location. Let me give it a try, can I?
Aosta: You...are not qualified to do so.
Ralph: ...Speaking of which, there are quite a few people out there who are hunting for members of the Feather Clan.
Aosta: They are a rare and exquisite race after all. There are those who do it for the money, and some who just treat them as high-level rune creatures.
Aosta: However, my objectives are not so simple and vulgar.
Ralph: Yeah, professor Clovis was always quite the eccentric personality, even in the past...
Ralph: Let's not talk about this. Are you missing any ingredients? I'll go buy them.
Aosta: The list is right there.
Aosta: So that guy decides to not come back...another worthless piece of trash.
Aosta: Some of the stone shards are missing. Did that guy take them? Could it be that the Feather Clan blood samples are also...?
Aosta: So a rune that explodes when coming in contact with air?
Aosta: Duped...that bastard Lavande...
